    "updated_at": "2017-04-19T09:14:24Z",
    "body": "> When running navigator.storage.persist();, nothing seems to happen.\r\n\r\nCan you expand on what you expect to happen ? \r\n\r\n> Note that the quotas are the same as before, with everything in temporary storage.\r\n\r\nThe spec doesn't state that quotas have to be increased when a storage has been made persistent, its just the storage will not be evicted unless there is an action performed by user explicitly. \r\n\r\n> So what is the truth? Is the storage persistent or not?\r\n\r\nYes by default all origins in Electron are granted durable storage, so they are not evicted automatically under storage pressure."
  },
