    "created_at": "2017-04-19T09:24:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-19T09:24:52Z",
    "body": ">Can you expand on what you expect to happen ?\r\n\r\nI would expect the `navigator.webkitTemporaryStorage.` to report zero, and the `navigator.webkitPersistentStorage` to report the size of the stored data.\r\n\r\n>The spec doesn't state that quotas have to be increased when a storage has been made persistent\r\n\r\nThe quota is already the entirety of my drive's free space, I just thought it would move from \"temporary\" to \"persistent\".\r\n\r\n>Yes by default all origins in Electron are granted durable storage, so they are not evicted automatically under storage pressure.\r\n\r\nIf you're sure about this, then there should be no issue. I just wonder why `navigator.webkitPersistentStorage` is telling me otherwise."
  },
